The weave is plain [warp-faced simple tabby] and the threads are S-spun and S-spliced; the stitch gauge is warp c.39 ends per 10mm and weft 13 picks per 10mm. Edges are torn, except where hemmed. Possibly from a very early mummy.

description.value: Textile fragment; long rectangle of linen cloth; medium-fine quality.  Plain with a pink tinge where it is unfaded - traces of safflower dye(?). Some green-ish stains and small brown stains are present. Edges are torn; fraying at the sides. The weave is plain [warp-faced simple tabby] and the threads are S-spun and S-spliced; the stitch gauge is warp c.28 ends per 10mm and weft 15 picks per 10mm.
